3. Base installation inclusions: Inverter/Battery. The inverter is mounted within 15m of the electrical switchboard. The supplementary/expansion [DC] battery must be vertically integrated or within 3m of the foundation battery stack or inverter. Additional installation costs ›

4. WA Battery Rebate. The value of the Residential Battery Scheme is applied as a $130 per kWh point-of-sale discount up to 10 kWh (usable kWhs) of storage capacity, with a requirement to join the Synergy or Plico VPP. Customers can opt out of this rebate and add the value to the advertised battery price.

5. National Battery Rebate. The National Battery Booster Program’s value is applied as a point-of-sale discount valued at $38 per certificate after trading fees. Request a preliminary quote for the total system cost (including GST) and incorporated pricing for the itemised rebate.

EV charger terms:

Tethered EV chargers are those with a cable attached to the EV charger. This format is a Type 2 AC connector suitable for new electric vehicles. The Sigen DC EV charger comes tethered with a CCS2 connector, also suitable for new electric vehicles.

Untethered EV chargers are those in which the cable connecting the charger to the vehicle is a separate component, sold separately. This EV charger type suits either:

  • Solar inverter energy ecosystem alignment
  • Public areas and
  • Older model electric vehicles that require a Type 1 AC connection
